  "title": "Communication, Accessibility, Professionalism, PBQs, and Exam Defense",
  "description": "A final support shift includes an anxious user, language and access needs, ambiguous evidence, a safety stop, competing priorities, a simulated performance task, and pressure to claim certification readiness from memorization alone. Learners cumulatively produce complete support defense and transfer plan through theory, guided work, debugging, transfer, retrieval, and assessment.",
  "order": 40,
